{
  "slug": "gh-cli",
  "name": "GH CLI",
  "type": "plugin",
  "description": "Intercepts GitHub URL fetches and curl/wget commands, redirecting to the authenticated gh CLI.",
  "longDescription": "Plugin with 1 skill (`using-gh-cli`) and 4 hooks that intercept `WebFetch` and Bash `curl`/`wget` calls to GitHub domains, suggesting authenticated `gh` CLI equivalents instead. Covers repos, issues, PRs, releases, raw content, and API endpoints. Includes 6 reference docs for `gh` subcommands and a `SessionEnd` hook that auto-cleans cloned repos from temp directories. Silently passes through when `gh` is not installed.",
